questions.fact: AI models often inherit and reflect the biases present in the data they were trained on, and researchers are actively developing strategies to identify, understand, and mitigate these biases.

questions.fact: AI models often inherit and reflect the biases present in the data they were trained on, and researchers are actively developing strategies to identify, understand, and mitigate these biases.

questions.fact: AI models often inherit and reflect the biases present in the data they were trained on, and researchers are actively developing strategies to identify, understand, and mitigate these biases.

questions.fact: AI models often inherit and reflect the biases present in the data they were trained on, and researchers are actively developing strategies to identify, understand, and mitigate these biases.

questions.myth: All content generated by AI is inherently and completely original, ensuring that it can never contain any elements or resemblances to copyrighted works or existing intellectual property.

questions.fact: Model distillation is a technique where a smaller, more efficient AI model is trained to replicate the behavior of a larger, more complex model, retaining much of its performance while reducing computational overhead.
questions.myth: The only viable method for enhancing the performance and capabilities of AI models is to continuously increase their size and the number of parameters, making them larger and more complex.
